    "narrative": "Our offensive engine for today\u2019s slate is anchored by **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **Corbin Carroll** (72.32), who provide the optimal synergy of favorable park factors and high-upside matchups. **Mickey Moniak** benefits immensely from a soft target in Sasaki, leveraging a +19% SP skill advantage and a +14% park bump to earn our highest daily efficiency score. Similarly, while facing a tougher arm in Gausman, **Corbin Carroll** remains an essential start; his elite sprint speed profile remains the cornerstone of our SB-focused strategy, and his strong xwOBA metrics suggest he can overcome the arm talent on the mound. **James Wood** (68.56) and **Austin Riley** (66.69) round out the top tier, with **James Wood** capitalizing on a leadoff spot that maximizes his exposure to potential scoring opportunities.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s card involved the utility spot, where **Alex Freeland** (53.65) narrowly missed the final cut. While **Alex Freeland** saw a significant boost from park factors and his switch-hitting versatility, his placement at the bottom of the order (-8% adjustment) dragged his efficiency below the established threshold for our starting nine. Consequently, he remains benched in favor of the higher-leverage opportunities presented by **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Trevor Story**. We are also keeping a close watch on **Tyler Soderstrom** (56.31); while he is currently active, his score is marginally above our floor, and the platoon disadvantage against Schultz suggests he is the first candidate to be pulled if we need to optimize for defensive stability late in the day.\n\nRisks today are centered on the platoon-heavy nature of our lower-scored starters. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (53.63) faces a stiff challenge against the handedness of Weathers, and any mid-game tactical shifts could impact his floor. Furthermore, while **Brice Turang** (58.40) projects well due to P\u00e9rez\u2019s delivery characteristics\u2014which historically grant a 100% stolen base opportunity profile\u2014the lack of elite power means we are entirely dependent on his legs and plate discipline. We remain sidelined on **Luis Campusano** and **Jose Caballero**, as their respective matchups against high-skill arms Urena and Ragans suppress their offensive ceilings well below the utility required to displace our current starters.",
